11 December 2014Minister of Communications, Ms Faith Muthambi adopted ward 14 in Willow Fountain, Imbali township, after realising challenges experienced by the people in this township.This visit emanates from the Presidential Imbizo with was held in Msunduzi, Pietermaritzburg on 30 September 2014.The Minister is back here, doing a door to door delivering; Christmas gift hampers to the indigent families in this area. Minister Muthambi will also be visiting the communications workers that keep these areas empowered with government information to improve the people s lives.Members of the media are invited to join the door to door and the factory visit.Date: 12 December 2014 Time: 09h00-16h00 Venue: Willow fountain War room; Ward 14 Imbali TownshipEnquiries: Ayanda Holo Cell: 061 488 0634 Follow the Minister on Twitter @faithmuthambiIssued by the Ministry of Communications